      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "A small-pad hauler fit that keeps a fast-recovering bi-weave and enough boost to break an interdiction, then fills every remaining slot with cargo. Initial is buy-only with a token shield; A-rated is the trade baseline; Engineered applies a range-and-escape pattern to the cores while keeping the ~84 t protected hold. The Dolphin defends by leaving, not by fighting — it flies unarmed and survives on speed.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Range and escape, not tonnage",
            "text": "The Dolphin can't out-haul a real freighter — nine small optionals top out near ~88 t all-cargo, ~84 t behind a shield. Its case is a light hull that jumps well and boosts clear of pirates. Keep the bi-weave and two Heavy-Duty boosters for contested lanes; the two small weapon hardpoints stay empty because the mass buys nothing a run can't."
          },
          "notes": {
            "TinyHardpoint1": "First Heavy-Duty booster multiplies the thin bi-weave's raw MJ — the cheapest survivability a light hauler can buy.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Second Heavy-Duty booster; two is plenty for a ship that escapes rather than tanks.",
            "TinyHardpoint3": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and a cool signature.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rate for headroom on the coolest hull in the game; Low Emissions plus Thermal Spread keep heat and signature down for a quiet trader.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rated + Dirty Drive Tuning give the boost speed to break a pirate interdiction — the Dolphin survives by leaving.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "The whole trading edge on a light hull: A-rated with Increased Range and Mass Manager turns routes into fewer, longer laden hops.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass, Lightweight trims more laden range; life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "D-rate is enough with no guns; Engine Focused plus Super Conduits feed the boost-and-run escape.",
            "Radar": "Drop to D and go Lightweight — a trader needs no sensor range, so bank the mass as jump range.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock C tank sized to the FSD; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size5": "Optional — the biggest single cargo slot; the bulk of the hold. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot02_Size4": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot03_Size4": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot04_Size3": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot05_Size2": "The landing-and-escape shield; a bi-weave (Reinforced + Fast Charge) recovers fast under fire. Pull it for a class-2 rack on safe runs.",
            "Slot06_Size2": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot07_Size2": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot08_Size1": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot09_Size1": "Optional — adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable."
